CI â€“ Continuous Integration
Imagine a group of developers working on the same app. Everyone writes code, right?
With CI, whenever someone finishes a piece of code, they push it to a shared place (like GitHub).
Then, automatically:
The code is checked
It is built (like packaging the app)
And tested to see if anything is broken
This happens every time someone updates the code.
âœ… So, CI makes sure all the code works well together and we catch mistakes early.
ğŸš€ CD â€“ Continuous Delivery / Deployment
Now that the code is tested and ready, whatâ€™s next?
With CD, that tested code is:
Automatically sent to a staging or production environment
No need to do manual steps each time
There are two types:
Continuous Delivery â€“ Code is ready to go live, but we press the final â€œGoâ€ button manually.
Continuous Deployment â€“ Code goes live automatically if it passes all the tests.

